    "summary": "I am a physicist and have a professional doctorate in applied mathematics.\nI have more than 20 years of experience as a scientist and technology developer in the security printing industry and central banking community. I have been employed by:\n-\tJoh. Ensched\u00e9, the national banknote / high security printer of the Netherlands\n-\tthe currency development team of the Central Bank of Canada (BOC)\n-\t(the technical committee of) the international Central Bank counterfeit deterrence group (CBCDG), as a representative of the Bank of Canada and the Dutch Central Bank (DNB).\nSince 5 years I have been an independent consultant with expertise on security documents. During this time I continued my the participation in the CBCDG, supporting the technical development and maintenance of the counterfeit deterrence system (CDS) for banknotes. \n\nIn the course of my career I have worked in research and development on several innovative digital and analogue security technologies.  The main fields of interest of this research are:\n- graphical security elements for preventing counterfeit of documents and protection of branded products \n- digital watermarking and image coding technologies \n- (biometric) identification systems \n- processing systems / sensors for automatic inspection of, both newly printed and circulated, banknotes \n- optical / graphical and machine readable security- and counterfeit deterrence features\n\nThe technologies that I (co-) invented and developed are based on basic principles of signal analysis and image processing, in combination with knowledge of the properties of scanning and printing equipment. I have published articles in peer-reviewed papers / journals on my scientific work and presented at international conferences. \n\nAlso, I have proposed, specified, managed and  participated in carrying out development projects for advancement of the CDS \n\nIt is my intention and ambition to continue my work on the subject of my expertise or in a related field \n",
